                <p>To calculate the z-value and p-value for a sample of size n and sample mean
                        <m:math overflow="scroll">
                        <m:mrow>
                            <m:mover>
                                <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                                <m:mo>¯</m:mo>
                            </m:mover>
                            <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                            <m:mn>550</m:mn>
                        </m:mrow>
                    </m:math>, enter the function below into R:</p>
                <code>significance = function(n)</code>
                <code>{</code>
                <code>z = (550-500)/(100/sqrt(n))</code>
                <code>paste("n = ",n,", z = ",z,", p-value = ",1-pnorm(z))</code>
                <code>}</code>
                <p>Then execute <code>significance(n)</code> for n = 5, 6, 7, ... until the result
                    is significant.</p>
                <p><em>Note: Using
                            R<?oxy_delete author="mmyers" timestamp="20101127T223207-0500" content=" - "?></em><?oxy_insert_start author="mmyers" timestamp="20101127T223225-0500"?>&#8212;<?oxy_insert_end?>you
                        can test all the values of n from 5 to 14 by entering
                            <code>significance(5:14)</code>. </p>-->
